<h3 id="surround-yourself-with-worthwhile-stories">Surround yourself with worthwhile stories</h3>
<p>I‚Äôve given up on the need to be a reader. I have a strong confirmation bias for the idea that I don‚Äôt read enough to justify the literature degree I have. Because of it, I see people basking in the light of the books they‚Äôre reading everywhere I go. Six weeks in the Algarve with no books except the Bible I didn‚Äôt touch did wonders for me. Instead of my usual feelings of guilt, I‚Äôm more discerning about the stories with which I surround myself. Life is too short to spend it feeding my brain and soul with things that don‚Äôt make me feel better, more excited, and more curious about life. This made it easy to skip <em><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Them_(TV_series)#Reception">Them</a></em>,  <em><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2022/12/10/opinion/the-whale-film.html">The Whale</a></em>, and <em><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Where_the_Crawdads_Sing">Where the Crawdads Sing</a></em>.</p>

<h3 id="firstly-im-a-designer">Firstly, I‚Äôm a designer</h3>
<p>In 2022 I realized that I don‚Äôt want to be a Product Manager. Since 2020 I‚Äôd been dabbling in the field, combining it with Design Management at my place of work, Leeruniek. Working as a Product Manager taught me volumes on strategic decision-making, big-picture thinking, and motivating an entire company behind a roadmap. It made me stellar at knowledge work. Sadly, it didn‚Äôt leave me enough room to do the things I truly love: product research and design, and the operational and leadership aspects associated with them. After my extended sick leave, I‚Äôm reintegrating back at work, thoroughly enjoying the researcher and designer I once again have become.</p>

<h3 id="other-things-i-learned">Other things I learned</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Food is cool, but I must chill:</strong> with an eating disorder that masked itself as a snobbish foodie for well over a decade, I am wise to be careful when engaging with kitchen projects. After coming back from Portugal, a major shift has been the time I spend in the kitchen. The lesson is that weeknight dishes don‚Äôt have to take longer than an hour to prepare. I‚Äôve committed to this with varying degrees of success.</li>
  <li><strong>Dogs aren‚Äôt so bad after all:</strong> if you know me in person, one thing you will understand is that, historically, I‚Äôm known to hate dogs. Bill Murray once noted that he‚Äôs ‚Äúsuspicious of¬†people who don‚Äôt like dogs‚Äù, and I‚Äôve always proudly countered that with ‚Äúdon‚Äôt trust people who are suspicious of people who don‚Äôt like dogs‚Äù. That being said, 2022 gave me the soft eyes required to decide with Anja that we will be making an effort to welcome a corgi into our home.</li>
</ul>

